ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ValueRange: American Indian/Alaska Native; Asian; Hawaiian or Pacific Islander; Black or African American; White; More than one race; Unknown or not reported; Other Non-White; Other

ElementDescription: Total of Section B - Non-Verbal: Qualitative Abnormalities in Communication
Total of Section B - Verbal: Qualitative Abnormalities in Communication
Total for Section A: Qualitative Abnormalities in Reciprocal Social Interaction
Total of Section C: Restricted, Repetitive, and Stereotyped Patterns of Behavior
Social Affect Total (used only with 2007 scoring algorithm)
Notes: In module 1 no words, equals A2 + A8 + B1 + B3 + B4 + B5 + B9 + B10 + B11 + 12. In module 1 some words, equals A2 + A7 + A8 + B1 + B3 + B4 + B5 + B9 + B10 + B12. In module 2, equals A7 + A8 + B1 + B2 + B3 + B5 + B6 + B8 + B10 + B11. In module 3, equals A7 + A8 + A9 + B1 + B2 + B4 + B7 + B8 + B9 + B10. Used only with 2007 scoring algorithm.

ElementDescription: Restricted and Repetitive Behavior Total (used only with 2007 scoring algorithm)
Notes: In module 1 no words, equals A3 + D1 + D2 + D4. In module 1 some words, equals A5 + D1 + D2 + D4. In module 2, equals A5 + D1 + D2 + D4. In module 3, equals A4 + D1 + D2 + D4. Used only with 2007 scoring algorithm.

ElementDescription: Name of IQ test given to participant
Estimate of the individual's verbal ability
Notes: Estimate of the individual's verbal ability and consists of both Deviation IQs (i.e. IQs derived from standard scores) and Ratio IQs (i.e. IQs derived by dividing verbal mental age by chronological age for individuals who were not able to obtain a Verbal Deviation IQ).

ElementDescription: This variable indicates whether the verbal iq reflected in the variable core_descriptive.ssc_diagnosis_verbal_iq is a deviation or ratio IQ
Notes: 1 =  Deviation; 2 = Ratio. This variable indicates whether the verbal iq reflected in the variable core_descriptive.ssc_diagnosis_verbal_iq is a deviation or ratio IQ; this information is provided for investigators who would like to report the proportion of each type of IQ comprising the sample.  A value of 1 indicates that the IQ is a deviation IQ; a value of 2 indicates that the IQ is a ratio IQ (see description of core_descriptive.ssc_diagnosis_verbal_iq above for more information).

ElementDescription: Estimate of the individual's nonverbal ability
Notes: Estimate of the individual's nonverbal ability and consists of both Deviation IQs (i.e. IQs derived from standard scores) and Ratio IQs (i.e. IQs derived by dividing nonverbal mental age by chronological age for individuals who were not able to obtain a Nonverbal Deviation IQ).

ElementDescription: This variable indicates whether the nonverbal iq reflected in the variable core_descriptive.ssc_diagnosis_nonverbal_iq is a deviation or ratio IQ
Notes: 1 =  Deviation; 2 = Ratio. This variable indicates whether the nonverbal iq reflected in the variable core_descriptive.ssc_diagnosis_nonverbal_iq is a deviation or ratio IQ; this information is provided for investigators who would like to report the proportion of each type of IQ comprising the sample.  A value of 1 indicates that the IQ is a deviation IQ; a value of 2 indicates that the IQ is a ratio IQ (see description of core_descriptive.ssc_diagnosis_nonverbal_iq above for more information).

ElementDescription: Estimate of the individual's overall cognitive ability
Notes: Estimate of the individual's overall cognitive ability and consists of both Deviation IQs (i.e. IQs derived from standard scores) and Ratio IQs (i.e. IQs derived by dividing their averaged mental ages by chronological age for individuals who were not able to obtain a Full-Scale Deviation IQ).

ElementDescription: This variable indicates whether the full scale iq reflected in the variable core_descriptive.ssc_diagnosis_full_scale_iq is a deviation or ratio IQ
Notes: 1 =  Deviation; 2 = Ratio. This variable indicates whether the full scale iq reflected in the variable core_descriptive.ssc_diagnosis_full_scale_iq is a deviation or ratio IQ; this information is provided for investigators who would like to report the proportion of each type of IQ comprising the sample.  A value of 1 indicates that the IQ is a deviation IQ; a value of 2 indicates that the IQ is a ratio IQ (see description of core_descriptive.ssc_diagnosis_full_scale_iq above for more information).
